A flag indicating whether anonymous users are allowed to vote.

Allows your site to capture votes on different topics in the form of multiple choice questions.

Are you sure you want to delete this poll %poll
Are you sure you want to delete this vote for %poll
Can always view poll results without voting, even when that feature is disabled on a poll.

The Poll module can be used to create simple surveys or questionnaires that display cumulative results. A poll is a good way to receive feedback from site users and community members. For more information, see the online handbook entry for the Poll module.
The length of time the poll is set to run.
The number of votes received by the winning poll answer.
The number of votes that have been cast on a poll.
The percentage of votes received by the winning poll answer.

Users can create a poll by clicking on Add a poll on the Polls page, and entering the question being posed, the answer choices, and beginning vote counts for each choice. The status (closed or active) and duration (length of time the poll remains active for new votes) can also be specified.
Vote form of the poll or the results depending on current user.
When the poll was created, as a Unix timestamp.

You can visit the Polls page to view all current polls, or alternately enable the Most recent poll block on the Blocks administration page. To vote in or view the results of a specific poll, you can click on the poll itself.
Your vote could not be recorded because you did not select any of the choices.
Your vote for this poll has already been submitted.
